Class HashSet<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc316.dsa.set.AbstractSet<E>
      • edu.ncsu.csc316.dsa.set.HashSet<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - generic param
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Set<E>, java.lang.Iterable<E>
    public class HashSet<E>
extends AbstractSet<E>
    Hash set extends abstract set Since our hash map uses linear probing, the entries are not ordered. As a result, we do not restrict our hash set to use Comparable elements. This also gives you an option if you need a set to manage elements that are*NOT*Comparable(versus a TreeSet)
    Author:
    sanjana cheerla
